AFGHANISTAN'S GOVERNMENT still struggles for legitimacy after 18 years and almost a trillion dollars spent fighting the Taliban; we ask why. A list of the world’s ultra-rich reveals that a disproportionate number of female self-made billionaires are from China—but the trend isn’t set to continue. And we examine why American presidential libraries are so controversial, and why Barack Obama’s is no exception. Runtime: 22min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn